Package: geomoz
Type: Package
Title: Geospatial Data for Mozambique
Version: 0.1.1
Authors@R: c(person("Hélder Gonçalves Félix", "Traquinho", email = "heltrakinho@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")), person("Geolithica", role = c("cph", "fnd")))
Description: Provides easy access to geospatial data for Mozambique,
    including administrative boundaries (provinces, districts, admin posts, villages)
    and geological data. Inspired by the geobr package for Brazil, but focused on
    Mozambique. Data is automatically downloaded from Hugging Face.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends: R (>= 4.0.0)
Imports: sf (>= 1.0.0), dplyr (>= 1.0.0), httr2 (>= 0.2.0), jsonlite
        (>= 1.7.0), rappdirs (>= 0.3.3), tools, utils
Suggests: ggplot2 (>= 3.3.0), leaflet (>= 2.1.0), testthat (>= 3.0.0),
URL: https://github.com/geolithicamz-hub/geomoz-r
BugReports: https://github.com/geolithicamz-hub/geomoz-r/issues
SystemRequirements: GDAL (>= 2.0.0), GEOS (>= 3.3.0), PROJ (>= 4.8.0)
Config/roxygen2/version: 8.0.0
